<HEADLINE>
FT  13 NOV 93 / National Savings bring in Pounds 435m
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
NATIONAL SAVINGS brought in a net Pounds 435m in October, up from Pounds
275m in September and Pounds 227m in August. Gross product sales were Pounds
879m and accrued interest was Pounds 182m. Repayments were Pounds 626m.
As in September, the highest contribution came from income bonds. National
Savings introduced tiered rates for larger investments in August and gross
sales of income bonds have now reached their highest level for 3 1/2 years.
The total amount invested in National Savings at the end of October was
Pounds 45.9bn.
</TEXT>
